### Apply Custom Styles to Booker Embed Component

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/platform/atoms/booker-embed.mdx

The BookerEmbed component accepts custom styles through the `customClassNames` prop. This prop is an object that allows for styling the root element and nested components using predefined keys. It enables granular control over the appearance of various parts of the booker, such as the container and date picker.

```javascript
import { BookerEmbed } from "@calcom/atoms";

export default function BookerEmbed( props : BookerEmbedProps ) {
  return (
    <>
      <BookerEmbed
        ...
        customClassNames={{
          bookerContainer: "bg-[#F5F2FE]! [&_button:!rounded-full] border-subtle border",
          datePickerCustomClassNames: {
            datePickerDatesActive: "bg-[#D7CEF5]!",
