### Secure Next.js Page Authorization

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/agents/knowledge-base.md

Illustrates how to implement authorization checks directly within Next.js `page.tsx` files in the App Directory. This ensures that sensitive content and routes are only accessible to authorized users by validating session information before rendering protected content. It avoids placing these checks in layout components.

```tsx
// app/admin/page.tsx

import { redirect } from "next/navigation";
import { getUserSession } from "@/lib/auth";

export default async function AdminPage() {
  const session = await getUserSession();

  if (!session || session.user.role !== "admin") {
    redirect("/"); // Or show an error
  }

  // Protected content here
  return <div>Welcome, Admin!</div>;
}
```
